<br>
Yeah the high end guilds have already killed the high end mobs in Luclin.<br>
But did we find any Epic armor yet?<br>
Does anyone possess the Vex THal Key?<br>
Do you guys raid Plane of Underfoot frequently?<br>
<br>
Thats just a few examples. No, it is all not even implemented, but thats exactly my point. <br>
<br>
Even without new expansions, there is still 34985 things that is broken or not implemented yet. Once Verant is able to cut the 'debugging of Luclin' since it IS debugged, they'll have time to implement the missing things. Epic Armor, new planes, new quests, putting sleeper back to sleep, fix the Vulak Ring...<br>
<br>
We all know that its dozens of things that need to be done.<br>
<br>
I agree that the Luclin zones are not too impressive. The outdoor zones look not really exciting to me. You have a flat area with a few mountains and a standard texture on it and then you put some random strange looking plants on it which look completely out of order compared to the ground texture. but then, maybe they tried to make it look as a real moon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyways. They announced that Luclin s not a high end expension. Still there are at least 5 zones every lvl60 can get exp. There even are some zones you do need a raiding force to get through at lvl60. <br>
<br>
Not all questions concerning Velius have been answered, there are still some missing things. DOn't forget PoM for example.<br>
<br>
And besides all this, even without new things, EQ has so much to offer, if you are not a powergamer and have 300 days played, you sure didn't see it all yet.<br>
<br>
SOme of you may just have to remember that EQ is not just collecting loot and killing the highest mob. If you go to Luclin, kill the highest boss mob and then declare Luclin as defeated and solved, then you miss something in the idea of EverQuest IMO...<br>
<br>
<br>
I give EQ at least 5 years if VI doesn't get broke or something. <br>
<br>
There is this game from VI, which they invented as a test for EQ. Tanarus. Its an easy Tank game that I played for over 3 years. They tested the platform for EQ with it. <br>
However, this game exists since 97. <br>
You have a few arenas which you cant leave, you cant buy or sell anything, you just pick a tank and go shoot. <br>
Since 5 years, the same thing. Really nothing complicated or deep. But its still up. They dont have many updates and patches, but it is still up. Its even FREE now, so VI doesnt make money with it, it loses money with it. Still, people like it and play it. <br>
It takes long and much to take an online game off the net. Cause you would in any way make many people sad. With EQ it would always be many 10k people. Atm even half a million. Maybe in 5 years just 100k, and still then, why should Verant take a game off the net which has 100k subscribers? <br>
They might at one point stop making patches, not bring out any new expansions, but they will keep it running.<br>
<br>
